qas.question: What is the name of the location cited by Ptolemy that is believed to have been located near modern Plymouth?
Where have Middle Iron Age remnants been found?

context: Upper Palaeolithic deposits, including bones of Homo sapiens, have been found in local caves, and artefacts dating from the Bronze Age to the Middle Iron Age have been found at <a1_0>Mount Batten<a1_0/> showing that it was one of the main trading ports of the country at that time. An unidentified settlement named '<a0_0>TAMARI OSTIA<a0_0/>' (<a2_0>mouth/estuaries of the Tamar<a2_0/>) is listed in Ptolemy's Geographia and is presumed to be located in the area of the modern city.
